\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Your name please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 George Alfred Doyle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}20 Longford Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Liverpool{\*\xmlclose} 8.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Your marital status?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 The year of your marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 1929.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 The year of your birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 1901.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}50 Bickerton Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Liverpool{\*\xmlclose} 17.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 According to what my mother told me, I was only a few months old when we moved from there to Wavertree, and we went to live in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Grosvenor Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, Wavertree. And we must have been there for about eighteen months or two years, when we moved from there to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Mathowan Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, in Wavertree, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Liverpool{\*\xmlclose}, 17. Then we moved from there to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Westdale Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} off {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Pickton Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 when I was about 4 1/2yrs. and we stayed there until my father had his accident and then we moved back to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}50 Bickerton Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} where I was born.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 So which was the house you lived in most years in your childhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}50 Bickerton Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 That was definitely the one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 In my childhood? That's rather a peculiar question, because I went into the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Bluecoat{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} when I was seven and I stayed there 'til I was fourteen and half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What about any more moves? Did you move again from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Pickerton Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} up to the end of 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. We were still there then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now do you remember why the family made these moves, from the very beginning, when you moved when you were only a few months old?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
The only reason as I can mention to that was that it was coming nearer to my father's employment. He worked in Lawrence Road way. That's the only reason as I'm aware of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Two sisters and one brother. The two sisters were older and the brother younger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How much younger than you was your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 3 years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And the next sister to you, how many years difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 She was 2 yrs older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And the sister after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Two-half yrs older again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How old was your father when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 29.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 He was born in Lark Lane, Liverpool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And what was his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Boot and shoemaker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did he have his own business or did he work for someone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 He worked for a gentleman by the name of Lunce in Lawrence Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did he have another job before or after he became a bootmaker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. Not to my knowledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did he also do any casual or part-time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Not until he went sick. Before nothing. After he went off sick he used to get boots and shoes to be repaired, even sent from Glasgow, as far away as that. And they used to come in sacks and he used to repair them and have them sent back again then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How did he have his accident?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
They were supposed to be cleaning out the works' cellar and the heavy bench was supposed to have fallen on to him and he went off sick at that,
 and before long he was moved into hospital. And it was there that they discovered that he had cancer. Well he went in and out of hospital about four times and in the end he was sent home to die. He died at home in 50 Pickerton Street.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well now, in this period of time, was this when he did his casual jobs at home? After he came home from hospital or before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well practically right up 'til the time when he was actually bedfast. He couldn't do any more then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 That's the only casual or part-time job he did? That is taking in boot and shoe repairing into his own home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Do you remember your father ever being out of work, apart from the accident, of course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 29. They were both about the same age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 From Liverpool. Lark Lane, area.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Had she any jobs before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. Not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did she work after she was married or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 She worked after my father became bedfast. Then she had to go out into domestic service, daily.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And she used to do this full time or part-time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Part-time. There were about three houses, and it was all over the dolly tub, and, and it was six in the morning 'til about ten at night.
 She'd go one day and do the washing and next day and do the ironing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And so three days a week she would work from 6 'til 10 at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And the other days she would spend at home. She didn't do any other jobs apart from that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now how long did she continue to do this up to 1918? Or up to the time of her death?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 She married the second time about 1913 or 14 and then she stopped working then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And did she ever work again, up 'til the time of her death?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Now you said your mother worked after your father died. Who looked after the children while your mother was at work? You said you were 6 when your father died, so that would make your younger brother 3, who looked after this little fellow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Well my elder sister went into a Home in Princes Road. I think it was called the Queen Alexander Home. And the other sister and myself, we went into the Bluecoat School. And there was only the youngest at home, so I presume that my mother's sister see
n to him while she was working. They lived right opposite each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Who ran the Home that you first sister went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 It was a Home for girls. It was an Orphanage at the top of Princes Road. I think it was run by charity, on similar lines to the
 Bluecoat school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
I should like now to ask you about life at home when you were a child, the time up to when you left school. Now I know that a lot of these years, obviously, with being away at school you are not going to be able to tell me a great de
al, but there are certain things you will be able to tell me. How many rooms were there in the house at Bickerton Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Six rooms. A sitting-room, the living room, and a back kitchen, and three bedrooms - two large and one small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What about toilet and bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Outside toilet and no bathroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Did anyone else besides your parents and brothers and sisters live in the house with you? Did you have any relatives or lodgers living with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. Not until mother married the second time. He was the only one that came into the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Was the washing done at home or sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 All of it done at home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your mother or father make or mend the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Not that I know of. My mother may have made some of the small clothes, apart from that I wouldn't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What about mending?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Oh she did all her own mending and she had a sewing machine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were the clothes new or second-hand when you got your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 New.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And what kind of shop would they have been bought in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I think they was all bought from the Liverpool Co-operative Stores.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 When did you have new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 When I was a small boy, in those days little boys were 
dressed in petticoats the same as girls and I went into the knickerboackers when I was about 3 1/2. And I remained in knickerbockers up 'til time of going in the Bluecoat School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And when would you have had new clothes, was there any special time of the year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I presume it was a case of when they was worn out, or we was too big for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your father make or mend shoes for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes. He made them and he mended them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 When would you have new shoes, would it be the same as for clothes or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Only when he considered they were worn out, beyond repair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house? Such as the cleaning or the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Not to my knowledge, he didn't have the time, he was always working on the boots and shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
So there wasn't anything you can recall him doing in the house, such as cleaning the fires or doing the decorating or any repairs or improvements to the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. No I don't think he was a handyman at all. Except for boots and shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did he dress or undress you and your brothers and sisters, or ever bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Or read to you, tell you stories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did he take you out without your mother at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes on occas
ions, yes. When I started school at Lawrence Road School in Wavertree he used to take me backwards and forwards to school, because at the same time he was going to work he could put me to school and pick me up at lunch time and take me home, brought me ba
ck again and the same for knocking off. I used to play about the school yard for half an hour or so until he was ready to take me home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Would he ever take you out anywhere without your mother, apart from taking you to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I wouldn't say witho
ut mother. He used to take us out to the park, there was no other means of anything in those days apart from going to Sefton Park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And he would take you without your mother or would your mother come along too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 On occasion, but the majority of times she would come as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Would he ever lock after you whilst she was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
No I don't think so. Because you understand it was rather a tough life with him being so sick and having to do this work of boots and shoes that he hadn't got the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you have any tasks you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Yes. Saturday's only. I used to go round the neighbourhood. Practically the whole of Egberts Close of our neighbourhood selling light cakes and buns w
hich my grandmother and auntie used to bake in the cellars. I went armed with two massive baskets, both loaded, and I used to go round from house to house selling these things. I was only six then. I was always sold out and my wages then would be 2d. for 
the full day's work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
How long did you continue to do this? Of course you were getting near the time when you were going to school, did you stop doing this when you went to School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Oh yes. Because once you went to Bluecoat School you were tied in. You couldn't do anything then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How after you left school you returned home didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you do any tasks, did you continue to help in the home in any way? Did you have any special jobs that you had to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Bits of decoration. And perhaps washing the dishes for mother, and such like.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Did your two older sisters help the younger ones with things they found difficult such as dressing or eating or look after them in any other way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did the younger children help the older ones in anyway, before they went away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your school days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well up to the age as I can remember I had to be in bed at eight o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 This would be before you went away to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And when you were at school what time did you have to be in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Summer nine o'clock. Winter eight o'clock. Very strict, very keen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your mother or any one else put you to bed? Up to the time you went away to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 My mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 At what age did you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 That was the first time I really put myself to bed, when I went to the Bluecoat School. Mother always supervised up 'til then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now did you share the bedroom or bed with anyone up 'til the time you went away to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Up 'til the time of going away to Bluecoat School the four of us slept in the one double bed, in the one room. I think we head to tailed it. I think that was the way the bed was laid out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 You say you had three 
bedrooms in the house at Bickerton Street, and your parents obviously slept in their own bedroom, so why wouldn't you have used the third bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I don't think there was a bed in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 In the kitchen, in a tin bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Every week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did this coincide with your bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes. When we bathed then we changed clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 In what we called the kitchen - the living room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No we always ate in the one room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 In the back kitchen. No, at first in the kitchen, she had the old fashioned grate with the oven and a gas ring.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 This is the same room where you ate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes. She did eventually change to a gas cooker about 1920.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Round about seven o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What members of the family were present for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Just the four children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And what about your parents would they eat breakfast with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Invariably father didn't he had to be getting ready to go out to work. Mother did. Father would have breakfast earlier on his own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Would he get up to get it himself or would your mother get up and get it for him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I think mother always got up first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 So what time would your father have had his breakfast if you had yours at seven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well not much different to us, because breakfast consisted of bread and dripping or
 a bit of toast and dripping, nothing cooked, there wasn't the money to provide for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you have anything cooked for breakfast on a Saturday or a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No I can't remember anything being cooked for breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What kind of things would you have had for dinner during the week?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
The majority of occasions it was scouse. It was made of a bit of that and then practically any vegetables at all. Potatoes, cabbage, carrots, turnips, onions, my mother used to put barley in. And it was a gener
al mixture of really fine cheap foods in those days. They were very tasty. Many a time the scouse had been what you might call 'blind' scouse - you couldn't find the meat! That was our chief meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What about Sunday, would you have had anything different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 She always had a small joint, roasted, and vegetables with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And what kind of puddings would you have had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Rice or Sago. It never varied. Oh, occasionally she used to make her own boiled puddings: ginger, lemon, apple, boiled puddings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did she ever make pastry at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Made all her own pastry, scones and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How what about your evening meal during the week? What would you have had for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Bit of bread and margarine, or a bit of bread and dripping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Never anything cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And what about your father would he have had a cooked meal in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well he had to do the same as us. After he became ill there wasn't any money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Up to the time he became ill, and things weren't quite as stiff, would he have had a cooked weal in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Oh yes, he would, when he was working. I presume mother would have as well. Invariably father and mother had their meal and then seen to the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes. But you never remember having a cooked meal at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your mother or father bake their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Yes mother baked her own bread. She always baked her own. Two big pan mugs they were put in front of the fire to raise and one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did she make her own jam or bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Yes she used to make some jam. I don't know about bottling fruit. One jam I do remember was damson. She always made her own damson jam. And I think she made her own marmalade.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did she make any pickles or wine or any medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Was any beer brewed for the family at the time when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your father or mother grow their own vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. We didn't have a garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did they buy any tinned or dried vegetables or fruit? When you were very small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No I don't remember her buying any tinned fruit when I was very young, but she used to buy the dried fruit for making her cakes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did they keep any livestock for the family? Any hens, pigs or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
When there was enough money to buy meat we had it in the souse, and when there wasn't it was just the vegetables, but we always had a joint on the Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you ever get some extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I couldn't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your father have more than anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well I supp
ose it was only natural at his age and us children, but I wouldn't know the amount of what he got but its only automatic that he got a little bit more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were you allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. Never. You sat to table to eat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 You had to eat what was put in front of you. If you didn't eat it at that meal you got it 'til such times it was gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What was your parents' attitude if you left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 It was put before you at the next meal and you just got on with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 If there was something on the table you wanted, like the salt, could you ask someone to pass it to you, or did you have to wait
 until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
You always had to ask for it. You weren't allowed to reach across a table. You had to ask the person who was nearest if they would pass it over to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No because there wasn't such a thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Definitely, yes. You had to hold your knife and fork in the correct manner, and you had to sit at the table with your back str
aight, you weren't allowed to lounge about or lean on the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 When the meal was completed by everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal? Apart from breakfast, when father wasn't eating with you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 We all sat together, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you always have the same places at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How was the meal served and by whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Mother served the meal and she went out into th
e back kitchen and she served them on to the plates and carried them in. From the saucepans on to the plates.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Where did your younger brother sit before he could feed himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 He had a high chair at the table and was fed at the same time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did she show you affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 She showed affection.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 If you had any worries would you share them with her or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well I don't know as I had any worries in my younger days. Abou
t the only worry I did have was that I was very poor at reading and I failed the first application to go into Bluecoat School on account of my reading, and then I had a teacher to myself at St. Michaels School that took me for the full day on reading only
 to get me right to pass into the Bluecoat School. Otherwise I don't know as there was any worries.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now what about your father was he an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did he show affection to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes. Yes he was a very jovial person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And if you had had any worries could you have shared them with him or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What was it about your father that you remember particularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What I remember mostly about him was taking me backwards and forwards to school. He was happy and contented person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes. Definitely. I would say that my mother was a person that was very strict on everything and everything had to be just so
. Although we were poor everything had to be just so. She was very keen and we had to be very polite to each other and we weren't allowed to talk to elderly people in those days. To be seen and not heard!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did they say, your parents, that you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
I don't think they ever said that. My mother would never interfere with the neighbours, if one of us had met with an accident she would say it's not worth it, that children while their parents are complaining 
together the children will be playing together. On the one occasion I did hit another small boy, I don't know whether he was smaller or the same age as myself, I got a crack for hitting him. I was given to understand that I mustn't fight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well I don't know that there was any discussions about that under the circumstances.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Do you think your parents brought you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. Except good clean living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 It was never used. I don't think I was old enough to know what swear words were before I went into the Orphanage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 When grown-ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No you weren't allowed to talk to the elders. Apart from speaking to relatives or ordinary plain conversation it was a case of No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 If you did something that your parents disapproved of, what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Father had a handy belt round his waist and mother had a small cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
If your mother had discovered you doing something she would punish you with the stick, and if your father had discovered some terrible thing he'd take the belt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now how often would this have happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Not very often. We were pretty well behaved as a rule.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What kind of thing would they have punished you for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I presume either being a little checky or obstinate, refusing to do something you'd been asked to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Can you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Not at home. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Tell me about something else that you recall at the School though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 In the Bluecoat School, yes. I was one of the bad boys of the school and admitted they had to be very keen and strict, b
ecause there was 250 boys, 150 girls, and you weren't allowed to mix. All in the one building but one side was the girls and the other the boys and you weren't allowed to mix. The only time we saw the girls was at meal time when we went into the big room.
 Meal time and at Church and at Sunday School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now tell me about this punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well it was a case of six of the best as it's called. Three on each hand with the cane. They came down heavy that your hands was bruised.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And what would they have punished you for for that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Any minor detail that they considered you were wrong. As a matter of fact in my estimation, as I have seen life since I left the school and the way children are treated at the present time, I've come to the conclusion 
that they were brutal. Any of the masters could chastise it wasn't left to the Headmaster. And if he caught you at the spur of the moment, perhaps whispering or anything like that, he came round with the cuff of his hand right behind the ear, and sent you
 flying. You always left your feet, and went over. And that's really speaking why I'm blaming my deafness. My sister was the same. The lady teachers were the same, they used to come round with their hand right behind the ear. And she was deaf in one ear.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And you definitely feel this is something to do with your deafness now, do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Because it was done very often was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes. As I say I was one of the bad boys, one of the dare devils.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Would you say that you received the i
deas you had about how to behave from both your parents, or did one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
I think mother played the most important part. In the way of looking after us and training us and everything. She was the major one. Father didn't have the time to be with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 When you were young when you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well you might have got a bar of chocolate or something like that. 1/2d bar of chocolate or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Not until I went into Bluecoat School and then you used to get a small present, not of great value, more like a small toy or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And any special tea or anything to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. Nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Tell me, while we're talkin
g about the Bluecoat School, is there anyone you can remember that you could go to there if you ever wanted, you know I spoke about how you felt about your parents and did they show you affection and if you had any worries when you were small could you ha
ve gone to your parents, well was there anyone in this School that you could think about like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
You had the priviledge of asking for an interview with the Headmaster. But I think I only had one interview with him and that was when there was a deat
h in the family, and of course I did it on my own. I applied to be allowed out of the School for the funeral. And the Headmaster contacted my mother and she said "No, she didn't want me there."
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Was there anyone there that you could go to when you were in trouble or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 You were really on your own, literally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Yes. They were very keen. Very strict. Everything was very regimented. Up at six o'clock. Dressed and out of the dormitory and straight down and get yourself w
ashed. And I think it was seven o'clock breakfast. And you came out from the breakfast and the teachers went in to have their breakfast. And we started school at eight. Eight 'til Twelve, and we had an hour's break for a meal and then back to school at on
e
 o'clock 'til five. You had your tea and the evening was your own. In the winter you had to go to bed at eight, in the summer it was nine. We had the big play yard. You weren't allowed to play on the sports field. You had the big concrete yard and if it w
ere wet weather you had the big play room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And what was the food like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Very poor. Very poor indeed. Insufficient for growing children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What would you have had for breakfast during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Two mornings a week it was just porridge. One
 morning it would be a piece of bread with cheese. The meals were always insufficient. You always felt hungry. You were always ready for the next meal. The only thing I couldn't face was the porridge because it had massive lumps like eggs in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What kind of think would you have had for your midday meal? Or your evening meal, at the Bluecoat School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
You had your main meal at twelve o'clock. I can remember Mondays was rice pudding only, with a small piece of bread and cheese, and nothing else. Tue
sday and Thursday, I think it was, you had beans in tomato ketchup and nothing with it, no pudding. You got stew one day a week. And I think it was stew on the Sunday. I can't remember ever having roast. If it had be roasted it had been put into the gravy
 and served from there. But we were so hungry we were glad to eat anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 So you didn't get a pudding every day then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. The rice pudding was a meal on it's own. Sometimes you'd be lucky and you might be able to get a second helping but if it 
were all gone at the first show there was no such thing as a second helping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And what about your evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 You got a think slice of bread about an inch thick, the full square, with margarine, which had been melted and pouted on to it in liqu
id form. Sometimes it'd be dripping. On a Sunday you got two thinner pieces of bread and butter, and sometimes one would have a bit of jam on. And you'd have a small piece of cake. That was Sunday only.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 That was teatime, did you get anything else to eat after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. That would be your last meal then 'til breakfast next morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And what would you have had to drink for breakfast and tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Either milk or cocoa. I've no recollection of ever having tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Can you remember anything you did with your mother or father together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Well not anyone in particular. We had quite a jovial time. Father was a very jovial person - he used to play the mouth organ and the clappers and he'd play an accordian. He used to black his
 face up and we used to have quite a bit of a sing song. Perhaps a few of the kiddies or the neighbours in. He could entertain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What about Christmas fare, what did you have to eat on Christmas Day when you were tiny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I couldn't remember prior to going into Bluecoat School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you have any presents? Did Father Xmas come down the chimney?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. We used to hang our socks up and you got an apple and orange and perhaps a small bag of sweets and that. That was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 You were saying your father played the accordian. Did he have his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And what else did you say he played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
The clappers, two bones, you put them between two fingers and you waggle them about, and you just have to know how to do them. He'd play the clappers while somebody else was making music.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Would anyone else in the family play these instruments or just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Nobody else in the family was musical minded, but a few friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well I suppose we all thought we were good so we all sang.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Apart from Christmas Day, this making music together, was this quite a common thing or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Oh yes it was quite a common thing when father was alive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
No I don't think so. No we had to go outside and make our own. They might have played snakes and ladders, and helped us to play dominoes or cards, that sort of thing, if they'd nothing else on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were there books or magazines or newspapers in the house when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 That is something I can't remember. There were some books, but they were chiefly prizes from Sunday School, and such like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Do you remember your mother or father ever reading when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Not apart from the newspaper. They always used to buy the Express which was the most popular in those days. They had this every day.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did they ever read aloud to you or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. I think they just read to themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I remember my own father's funeral although we didn't go. We stayed at home, we were too young to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Who attended his funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 All relatives. My mother had a sister and two brothers and there was either their husbands or wi
ves and they attended. I think there was two coaches, on that occasion. Because both my father's parents were living at that time and his brothers and sisters, but they couldn't all come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What kind of mourning clothes did the people wear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 They went into very deep mourning in those days. Everything was black, both men and women.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Can you describe any of the clothes that you can remember seeing to me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Just the ordinary black. The men wore the bowlers, and the women wore black from top to 
feet. Veils were very popular in those days, they wore a veil for the funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Can you remember them coming back to the house after the funeral or didn't they do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No, I can't remember them coming back. I can't remember anything else at all 
because we were sent to play with our cousins and friends while the funeral was on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were you taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Only to relatives and to one friend of my mother's. We used to go and visit, living so handy to one
 another we used to pop into anybody's house, 'cos they all lived so handy.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Would your mother take you, or would anybody else take you to visit relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No I don't think so. We just went on our own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 You wouldn't go as a family outing for instance at the weekend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No, apart from the one friend that my mother had, and she used to take us to visit about once every month or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were you taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 You explained he took you to school and brought you home and you occasionally went to the park with him with your mother. Didn't you?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Do you remember any other outings with your parents, Bank Holidays or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Once or twice we went to New Brighton, but apart from that No. \{
BLANK] I think at the Bluecoat School we had an outing to Beaumaris, North Wales, on the boat; and then we used to be taken to Calderstones Park one day, for a bit of recreation and sport an
d what not. But if you were in the Bluecoat School Band you went to Beaumaris twice - you went with the boys one day and you went with the girls another day. They never went together. I was in the band.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I was termed the handym
an. I learnt them all. I started with the tenor horn, then I got to solo tenor, and then I went on the cornet, then to soprano. Then I went on the euphonium and I went on the bass, I don't know as I done much with the trombone, but I played the clarionet.
 Father was very musically inclined. If there was anybody short I used to be taken off my instrument to go and replace them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now what did you go to Beaumaris for, to play in the band?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 To play in the band and it was a day's outing, on the boat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And where would you play in the band?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
We used to go on the tram cars down to the pier head, and we'd play the band leading the school down the old carriage way and we'd play the band right down to the boat and we'd play the band while we were on t
he boat. And we'd only get about twenty minutes break when you were called upon to play another couple of tunes on the boat. When we got to Beaumaris we didn't get much pleasure out of it because we used to go to the market square and we played there prac
t
ically the whole time we were in Beaumaris. I went into the band just before I was nine years of age and I carried on then right up, 'cos being a bandsman you were excused the cleaning part of the school. The boys and girls had to do all their own cleanin
g. Cleaning and scrubbing the corridors, bedrooms and all such like as that, and you were excused that because you were a bandsman, and always had band practice.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Not as a child, no. That was considered to be a
 good holiday to get a fortnight home from school twice a year. You got a fortnight in May and two weeks in September.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Your mother sent you and your sisters into these homes because she really couldn't afford to keep you at home, did it upset her a gr
eat deal, can you remember? When you left home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Well she didn't show it to us. She might have been upset but she didn't show it to us. Because we used to break down as soon as we got anywhere near the school. You had to carry your own box and if you 
couldn't get a tram car it was just too bad.. We had to walk right across Sefton Park from Lark Lane and by the time you'd got to the bottom of Penny Lane well there was no point of getting on tram car 'cos you was practically there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How many miles would that have been carrying your box?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
About a three and a half to four mile walk, and you were carrying your wooden box. It had to be made to a specification to the School's requirements. They all had to be the same size, with your names on. I've still got mine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What uniform did you wear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
You had trousers, waistcoat, and frock-tail coat, with a bib. And the girls they had dark navy material and a very big flared skirt and they wore the proper big bib. The clothes were quite comfortable to w
ear. And of course you had to clean them and repair them yourselves unless they were too big. If it wasn't too big a tear you had to go to the tailoress and she gave you a needle and thread and you had to get on with it. But of course if it was a big job 
she had to put it on the sewing machine and do it. And she used to supply mugs with rock ammonia and pads of clothing rolled into a tight bunch and you just dipped it in and you rubbed off any stains that was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And was this the only cleaning they got? They were never washed or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
No, they were never washed. And you got a new suit every two years. And you had three suits and they were handed down as they went on. You always had the special suit for Sundays, Sunday services, and you had 
the ordinary day time suit, and the other one was just a play suit, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days. This is before you went away to school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 That was the day I was always out selling light cakes and muffins, etc. all day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Oh yes, we went to Church in the morning, Sunday School in the afternoon, and Church again at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you have different clothes to wear on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Oh yes, always. Always had our best clothes, they were worn Sundays only.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 On Sunday, again, did you play games or did your parents think it was wrong to work or play on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 We weren't allowed to play on a Sunday. Sunday was a recognized religious day and you had to abide by it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What about doing any work at all on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Well apart from what mother done, a little bit of cleaning, she didn't do a great deal on a Sunday, she just tidied up and that was all that was done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your parents attend a place of worship or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 F
ather used to go to Church in the morning with us children, and invariably mother went to the Evening Service. Father didn't go to the evening service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What denomination was this Church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Church of England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Was this a regular Sunday thing, did you always go and did both your parents go to Church at least once a day, every Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 It was a regular performance. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And you went to Sunday School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were there any Sunday School outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Oh yes. We used to get some 
good Sunday School outings. Southport. Sefton meadows. And we used to have one over at Loggerheads. There were a choice of three places really where we used to be taken.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Once a year or more than once a year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Only once a year. They called it a tr
eat not an outing. It was very nice. The teachers and all the children they all went and more often than not you only got one decent meal when you were on those places, but you got a belly of buns and cakes and sandwiches and you were just taken on to the
 fields and the teachers organised sports for us. Races and such like. And they were always considered a very good day out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What other social activities were organised by the Church of England church that you attended and did you take part in any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
I belonged to the Church Lads' Brigade, while it existed, then we were taken over by the Kings Royal Rifles during the war. And we were put into khaki instead of the pill box. This was during the First World War from about 1916.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 When you were a little fellow, about 6 or 7, did you belong to the Lads' Brigade then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. I was too young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were there any other social activities that you took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. I was too young in the 
early days, and when I came back from the Bluecoat School I was too old. But of course you always had to be in the choir at the Bluecoat School, one evening I think it was a Thursday when the boys and girls come together to practice the singing for the ne
xt Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now did the Church of England that you went to run any temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Not for children but it did for adults.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were either of your parents a member of that club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Can you remember any activities of the temperance club at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you belong to any other club organised by the Church of England at all that you belonged to before you went to Bluecoat School?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. But afterwards I was one of those that helped to organize a men's club. I was about sixt
een then, and stuck to it 'til I got married. We had a gymnasium and billiards and quite a few indoor games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I think mother said it morning and night - just before the breakfast and at the end of the eveni
ng meal. But in the Bluecoat School it was said three times a day, before and after each meal.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes. Mother taught us to kneel at our bedside and say our prayers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And did you ever have family prayers together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Not to my knowledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Do you know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your parents talk about any issues or if they had any views about who should govern the country, or 
if they thought the working man had a square deal or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I don't think they were really interested, in politics at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Do you remember your father or mother voting in a General Election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No I can't remember them doing that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employers. Do you know if your father felt himself under that kind of pressure to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 You say your father wasn't a member of a political party. You don't remember him working for one of the parties at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Or your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Your parents didn't take part in any political activity at all then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. Not to my knowledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 When your parents were not doing their work, how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well they never finished doing their work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Not apart from the Mother's Union and the Guild.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And how often would she go to those meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 There was one on a Monday, I think, and the other on a Wednesday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now did she ever go out to enjoy herself at all, apart from these meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Not until later life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 When did your father get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Invariably round about eight o'clock time. He'd come home for his tea and went back again. It was always 12 or 16 hours a day. He'd come home about half-past four for his tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
I can't remember that he ever went out during the week. Invariably if he felt in one or his jovial moods he used to dress himself up and come out in the street, and the next thing the neighbours were there and we'd
 just have a little bit of a merry sing song. In the street. Oh yes, if he felt jovial, he'd black his face and put a fancy tie on, a dicky bow, and come out with his clappers or perhaps his accordian, and he used to change them according to what the othe
r
 neighbours'd be bringing out. If he saw somebody else had brought an accordian he'd put it back in, or if somebody had brought a mouthorgan he'd put his back in and he'd do the clappers then. And the neighbours they used to make quite a bit of fun. And t
hey sang. And the children enjoyed it, they all joined in. The children were all enjoying the same sort of function.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now did your father attend any clubs or pubs? Well you mentioned he went and had a drink at the weekend. Would this be Saturday and Sun
day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
He was not a member of any club. I don't know whether he went to the same public house or not, I don't know. And he went for a drink invariably only on a Saturday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did he go regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Mostly. If he felt well enough he went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your mother go too, ever, with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
I can remember my mother telling me that if she thought he'd stayed too long she used to take us children round pub and sit us on the seat and then shout in to him "Your children are there for you." And that 
was it, but she didn't actually go with him for a drink. She was a teetotaller. I don't think she ever tasted it in her life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your father take part in any sport? Did he attend the races or bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No I don't think so. I don't think he did. I ca
n't remember as how he was ever interested in betting he might have done on the side line, but something that we didn't know anything about.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs, such as boot, sick, funeral clubs, etc?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Mother a
lways was in funeral club, the Liverpool Co-operative, just a covering for death. She would organize this for both parents and children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 But no other clubs that you can recall apart from that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How did you get on with your brother and your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Very well indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Was there one you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Well really speaking there was. My sister that was in the Bluecoat with me, we were pretty close, we were. The one that was two years older than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 As a chil
d who did you play with up to the time you went to the Bluecoat School? Did you play with your brothers and sisters mostly or did you play with neighbours and friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Chiefly neighbours and cousins. My cousins lived a few houses up the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Where did you play mostly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 In the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Because you only had a yard. Did you ever play in the yard at the back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No we always went out into the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you ever play in other children's homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Or anywhere else? You didn't go into the park on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What games did you play, when you played out in the street, mostly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Marbles. Kick the can; if it was your turn to kick the can you'd kick the can, and as you kicked the can everybody scattered and 
you'd got to go and try and find them, just like hide and seek, and the first one you found it was their turn to go and kick the can, they were all called in then. Tick - ticking each other and dashing off. That was about the lot I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I don't think mother really objected.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your parents discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you belong to any youth organizations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Only the men's club attached to the Boys' Brigade, but that was when I was older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
I should like now to ask you about how you spent your free time when you were at school. Did you have any hobbies then? Now remember this will include the time that you were at the Bluecoat School as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
In the Bluecoat School I had the hobby of collecting foreign stamps. Also collecting butterflies and moths: I used to put them into a small box with a camphor ball and that killed them and 
then I used to spread their wings out on a block of wood that I had grooved, spread their wings out and pin them down on the block and then bind them with cotton so as they stayed like that, and then I used to put them on to a cotton wool pad and they wou
ld stay like that. I used to keep a piece of glass over the top to keep the dust off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you do anything else besides collecting stamps, moths and butterflies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I was a great player of chess. I used to play chess quite a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now did you keep any pets, either up to the time you went to School or after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now when you were young before you left school did you collect anything apart from the butterflies and the stamps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Cigarette cards, but apart from that nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you do any gardening at the School where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. You weren't allowed to. We had a gardener.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you go fishing or for walks or bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Bicycling after leaving school, but not before leaving school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Any walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well not e
xactly walking because you only had the play yard to go round and we used to trot round this play yard and it was estimated that eight times round the yard was a mile. And I've gone round forty and fifty times.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you do any fishing as a youngster?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you take part in any sports apart from running round the playground?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No we had none at the Bluecoat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you go to any theatres; concerts; music halls; or cinemas while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. On occasion they used to have a concert in the School but you were never allowed out to go to anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What sort of concert would they have given?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 When they did have them they used to bring somebody along, a gramophone and a few artists to sing a song.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 So it wasn't the children entertaining themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you enjoy them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well yes, I mean to say, anything for a change.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your parents give you any pocket money, now up to the time you went to Bluecoat and after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 In the Bluecoat School when we came home for our holidays they gave us about 2/- and of course that had to do you for the fortnight.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Your parents would give you this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 But you didn't have any pocket money whilst you were in the Bluecoat School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. You'd no means of spending it either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What about before you went in, can you remember if you got a regular amount?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. you'd get a 1/2d or a 1d for doing messages or something like that. But we didn't get a regular sum. 1/2ds and 1ds that was 
the limit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Sweets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after her house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. Definitely not.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No relations or friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Plenty of relations but they didn't give any assistance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage? Do you remember what happened when your younger brother was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well really speaking she was never ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 So you don't recall any time when she was in bed and anyone had to come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes practically all lived nearby. On my father's side and my mother's side, all lived nearby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How much did they see of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Very little. Mother used to 
see her sister who lived across the street. They used to be very friendly. But the others they never came to the house at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And did you ever used to go to their houses at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I used to go to their houses on odd occasions even when I was at the Bluecoat School and was never welcome.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 So your mother didn't go, it was only you that went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
I went on my own. Mother didn't go. But I was never welcome. If they were going to have their afternoon cup of tea with anyone I was told to go out and play while they had it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your parents have friends apart from the relatives that lived nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
My mother only had one friend, her name was Mrs. Spicer and she used to live in Westley Road where we lived and when we left Westley Road she lef
t and she went to live in Rathbone Road and to the best of knowledge if she's still living she's still there. We went to visit them a few years ago and they didn't seem to be all that enthusiastic so we didn't bother going any more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How much did your mother see of her when you were a small child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Every day.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your father have any particular friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Not that we were aware of. He just seemed to make friendship with everyone. No particular friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did he ever have any friends in or go and see anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did they share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes, they seemed to be all happy and contented.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were friends ever invited into the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. Only mother's one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No friends of your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Nor relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now when this friend of your mother's called in, would she have been offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 They might have had a cup of tea, about all, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did friends call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you have neighbours that called in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No, only that one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your parents go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No, apart from that one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 People often tell us that in those days they made their own amusements. Now on the odd occasi
on when your mother had a friend in, or you also mentioned Christmas time when you had people in; what do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 We made music.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you play any games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No I can't remember that we ever played any games.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups; in that time before 1918, did you think of some people belonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Could you tell me what the different ones were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
As I saw it then it was just a matter of boys and girls, either of their own sex or opposite sex, linked together and started knocking about together. You ignored them because you knew they were going out with three or fou
r boys or out with a girl or something, so you didn't bother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 But what different types of classes would you have thought there was at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 At that time, my idea was that it was stupid to tie themselves up into bodies and just associate with themselves. I felt it very silly.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What do you think they ought to have done then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
It would have been better if they'd have said, 'Now lads we're going to pictures or a theatre, anybody coming?' And all go together, those who wished to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Which class or group would you say you belonged to yourself, when you were a child before you left School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Course with being tied down to boys all the time in the School it was a sort of a problem to become associated with girls outside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What social class or group would you put yourself in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
More of the lone wolf type. I thought I was a little bit superior to the majority for the simple reason that I had been taught my manners and taught to behave, whereas the other children seemed to be allowed to be as they liked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Do you find it impossible to give it a name, the class or group you belonged to at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I wouldn't know what to call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What sort of people belonged to the same class group as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Only one chap and we cycled together for miles every weekend and eventually we worked together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 But can you think of any occupation that you think you could put as being in the same group as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. I don't know. I was a good simple living person.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Well I wasn't brought up with them, but when you left the Bluecoat School you were allocated a visitor which was an old Bluecoat boy, and you were supp
osed to go and see him once a month and have a talk and he would advise if you wanted advice or you could just discuss anything. Also, I had people to go and see regularly that was responsible for getting me into the Bluecoat School, they seemed to be ver
y
 interested. There was a Miss Vine from Egbert Road, and there was the Horsfall's family and their estate is now the Barracks in Egbert Road, and I had to see them every fortnight. They seemed to be very interested and I think the mother had the idea that
 
I was going to be trained as a butler and work for them, starting as a coach boy first and working my way up. But the more you saw of the people the more you learnt about them. Two of the daughters of Horsfalls definitely gave you the impression they were
 above, they belonged to a higher society and they were dictating to you all the time, sort of thing. Whereas on the other hand, the other two daughters were very friendly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 In what other ways would these two girls show they thought they were superior to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Just in their manner and speeches, and so on. They belonged to moneyed people and I was an orphan like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What social class or group do you think that family belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 The two that I mentioned I'd put them down as snobs. They thoug
ht they belonged to the top class. Very high opinion of themselves. Plenty of money, own coaches, stables, and everything in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Apart from this information which you have given me, can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort
 differently from people of another? Can you remember your parents, or anyone else who used any influence on you, not even to say it, but you got the feeling from them that you were expected to treat certain people differently from other types of people?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
No I don't think so. Only my own education in the Bluecoat School where we were taught to respect our elders, no matter who they were, we were taught to respect them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were you ever taught to touch your cap or show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 We al
ways took our cap, no matter who it was. Any stranger spoke to us and we took our cap off before we spoke. And we addressed them as 'sir' or 'madam' as the case might be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And what about people you knew and relatives you might have met in that period of time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 You still took your cap off, as a matter of respect.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 So you weren't told to be like this in respect of a particular type of person, you were told to do this to everybody you met?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 To everybody, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Was there anybody you called 'sir' or 'master' or 'madam' apart from this respect that you showed to every person older than yourself?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I addressed everybody the same. If I thought they were a 'miss' or a 'madam' or 'sir'. With the men it was always 'sir'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No I don't know of it. I can't say really that anyone did in the same manner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And you look back on this do you with any feelings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No I didn't look back with ill feelings, but I did have
 the idea there's something odd that I'm doing it and that nobody else seemed to be doing it. And at that age I just put it down well it's the training that we've had and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now in the district where you lived, which would have been the Lark
 Lane area, who were considered the most important people in that area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
In those days all round Sefton Park and the streets from Lark Lane and all that, they were all privately owned houses and no flats and they were all looked upon as high class peo
ple, moneyed people. There was Lords, and judges, and there was all sorts. But I think the most respected person of the lot was Canon Irvine from Christchurch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now was this particularly for the clerics or the clergy or for this particular man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Just for that particular man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 The clergy as a rule, would you not have included them in the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I daresay I would have done, but he seemed to be an outstanding person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What about other types of occupations of this type of 
important person, you've mentioned judges and Lords, what other occupations would these people have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
One person that my mother used to go and do the washing for lived in Waverley. Road and he was a jeweller. A high class jeweller from London Road. His own business. Another one was a barrister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you come into contact with any of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Canon Irvin regularly of course.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What with going to Church and he used to come to the Boys' Brigade. And the Men's club when it opened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 This was after you left School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What about during the time you were at School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
You didn't come into contact with anybody. The only people you saw when you were at School was Sunday afternoons at the Sunday afternoon Church service. And ordina
ry visitors walked right through the dining room. Your mothers were allowed to sit in the gallery while you had your meal but at the same time you weren't supposed to wave or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 You mean they weren't allowed to speak to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How often were your parents allowed to come and visit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Every Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And would they attend the afternoon Church service with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And would you be with them then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. The boys were two sides of the Chapel and the girls w
ere in the centre, and we were placed that way for the singing of the hymns, etc. But we could see our parents in the gallery and all the visitors and ordinary people they were down on a level with us. After the service was over we marched out to the dini
n
g room and then these people just walked through while we were having our meal and our parents were up top, but we weren't allowed to let on. We used to try and read their lips when they were trying to say something, if you could catch it, but you hadn't 
to let a teacher notice you were staring hard otherwise that was wrong. They knew that they were trying to say something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Why do you think they didn't let you talk to your parents on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I don't know it was just a ruling that they made. We 
were solely in their charge and they were going to make it their business that we were going to be that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What about shopkeepers, for instance, who did they associate with in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I wouldn't really know how to answer that. My mother us
ed to do all her shopping at the Liverpool Co-operative, so I didn't really know any privately owned shopkeepers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What about the clergy, who do you think they would have associated with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well Canon Irvin had his own private friends round the back, they were more or less business people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What about teachers, who did they associate with, who would their friends have been, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I couldn't answer because we never saw them in their private life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And what about farmers, who did they associate with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I wouldn't really know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What about employers who do you think their friends were, would you have any idea about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No not really. I think they kept to themselves. They didn't associate with the workers or anything
 at all. They was too much one sided in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now what sort of people would you say went to the Church and the Chapel? For instance, what sort of people went to your Church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 All very good people. I don't think there were anything particula
r about their occupations or their grading or anything. They just went to Church to pray and that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What about Chapel, did you ever come into touch with anyone who went to Chapel? And what sort of people went to Chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well tell
 me, when you were a child, up to the age you left school, was there any friction between Catholics and Protestants that you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I can only remember it after leaving School, because Bluecoat School was all Protestants. Afterwards, living in
 this locality, in the South end it was very bitter. That would be 1915 when I left School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Tell me about some of the things that you've heard and seen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Practically every weekend there was a street fight. After the public houses were closed and 
they came out there was always somebody as spoke out of turn and there'd be a street fight amongst the grownups. They were very bitter in this area one time. The Oatholics didn't seem to be liked by the Protestants. They seemed to put themselves into a se
cret service position - they didn't want to associate with Protestants.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Do you really blame the Catholics more than the Protestants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Oh yes, I did do, in this area. There were regular fights and of course all round here, Liverpool 8, at the top e
nd, they were what you might call lower class people. The poorer class people and people who used to like to go out and get drunk and that was always when the trouble started.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What kind of jobs would they have had do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well the majority would be working for the corporation and the docks - casual labour at the docks and such like as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And these were the types that mostly caused the trouble?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How where you lived, did all the people in the working class group have t
he same standard of living or would you say there were different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
I think they practically all had the same standard or living. They were all ordinary working people and really speaking there were nobody much better off than their next door neighbour. They were practically all one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What kind of family would you have put in that working class group, where you felt all the standards were the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 One person who lived in our street, her husband was in a fruit storage, a friend of mine 
his father was on the corporation, a dustman. I had an uncle who was a cooperer, lived in the same street. Another uncle who was an ex-seafaring man who worked for the dock board in the power station. They were absolutely mixed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 You felt they were all the same, their ways or living, and nobody had more than anyone else? Did you mean this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you ever think that one group felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. I didn't. Not in our neighbourhood. No. They all seemed to be pretty well on level footing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 You didn't, but did you think anyone else thought that they were superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well if they did they didn't show it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were some families thought of as rough and some families as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 The majority were respectable, you just got the odd one that were rough type.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well what would make them rough as opposed to the respectable ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well I'd think myself in those days when money was small it was where the fathers were going out drin
king all the time and neglecting the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And so it would not be because of their jobs, but because they didn't spend their money wisely?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes, that's right. They'd spend it on beer and because of that their children was allowed to rough it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Not to my knowledge there wasn't with myself. I didn't look down upon anybody myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Do you think any other people made a difference between labourers and craftsmen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
There used to be quite a little bit of talk, even if it was only fun, "Well you're only a labourer and I'm a tradesman and such like." But I don't know as it meant anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 This is what you've heard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And would you hear this often or not very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Well on the job on the railway it was used very often indeed. A driver on the railway in those days, he was looked upon as a big man and he was one of the best paid men in the country, as a worker. And he looked down on everybod
y even his own firemen, and labourers well they had to keep out of the way sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes or groups? Did they think of people differently in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No I don't think so. I think they treated everybody as one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class or group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No because she didn't have time. She was always very busy working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Nothing you can remember that would indicate what class she felt she was in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. I never heard her say she felt dissatisfied with the way she worked or anything at all like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Was it possible at that time to move from one class or group to another? And can you remember anyone who did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
I can remember a few of my mates that got jobs a little bit superior to some of the others. Whereas some had only gone as shop lads some had dropped into an office and they had the idea they were a little bit above. They thought they were 
the white collared men, put it that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And they felt themselves that they had moved from one social class to another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 That's right. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Do you remember anyone being described as a 'real gentleman' or a 'real lady'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Definitely. Canon Irvin. He was a'real gentleman.'
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Why would you call him that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
He was friendly to everybody and he treated everybody as his fold. I don't think he ever crossed a bad religion. He spoke to everybody that was in his parish. And about once a mont
h he used to go and visit everybody in his parish and it didn't matter what their creed was he went and spoke to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Can you remember anyone else who was referred to as a 'real gentleman' or a 'real lady'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 The only other one that I would say, 
was a Mr. Hughes that lived in Linnet Lane and he was in the timber business. They had their own business. He took full control of Boys Brigade and then the Cadets and he financed the organising of the Hens Club, etc. And he was a bachelor and just seemed
 to want to be amongst the working folk. I thought he was a real gentleman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Oh yes. They were all on foot in those days, apart from the mounted police they were all on foot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What did you think of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Well those that were attached to Lark Lane they were very good. Well knowing boys, boys can always get into mischief no matter who they are. Now the policemen up Lark Lane, they didn't bother taking you up to the statio
n or such like. They used to take you down the back and take their belt off, they used to wear belts in those days, and give you a hammering with their belt and say they'd tell your mother or father as soon as they see them, which they did. They used to g
o
 along to their parents when they met them in the street and say "Oh, I had your George misbehaving himself and I gave him a good hammering." And they'd say "So you should, thank you." And that was that. And they were respected for it. Even for the chap t
hat used to got drunk, they'd take him home. They wouldn't take him to the police station. They'd take him home and possibly give him a bit of a hammering at the same time. But they wouldn't prosecute him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your mother ever threaten to call a policeman if you were naughty? Were you ever afraid of them in anyway or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Never afraid of a policeman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What kind of a man do you think he was compared to the policeman of today?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I think they were better than what they are today because there
 are a certain type of policeman these days who are all out to make a case out of practically nothing. As long as they can make a case.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 So do you think he treated people well or badly in your opinion. The policeman when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I think he treated then very good. Very good indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well I didn't, my mother would, paying the rent like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you ever remember him coming to the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
I didn't really see him. I have been to their office, if mother wanted some repair work doing. They always gave a promise they'd do it but it always took them a long time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were they friendly or unfriendly to you at the office, when you went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 T
hey seemed friendly enough. One of the clerks that was in the office used to come round and collect the rent. Of course we got to know him. He was a very nice person but full of broken promises. If you asked for a job to be done he'd say it'd be done righ
t away and you had to wait months and months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Definitely. Always in my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 This was always there when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Up to when my mother married the second time and then things became a lot more comfortable for her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 But as far as you can remember in your childhood money was always short?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you ever go hungry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well we didn't really go hungry, but we might have been undernourish
ed because as I say it was only bread and margarine or bread and dripping, and perhaps a little bit of jam. You didn't have the substantial meals that was necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What other things indicated to you that money was short?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 You couldn't ask for a
nything in the way of boots or shoes or clothing or anything at all, because mother'd always say "When I've got a few coppers I'll get them." It made you realize there wasn't any money to spare.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
He was never out of work, but he was ill because he had an accident. Really speaking, I don't know as it made such a great deal, because the eldest..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What about money coming in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 To the best of my knowledge there was nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How would you have managed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well mother, she seen to all that. How she managed I wouldn't know, but as I say she had a broken back over a dolly tub.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 So you really feel that because your mother did this work when your father was ill, you didn't notice much difference in the money?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No, not the length of time he had been ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you ever get help from the Guardians or the parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. Only the Bluecoat School. Of course that was all charity. And the
 eldest girl was in the Queen Alexander Home, which was also run by charity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
When there was someone in the district whom the people disapproved of very strongly, was there any special way in which the rest of the people showed it? For instance do you 
remember anyone being made to leave by rough music? Have you ever heard that term? By rough music I mean banging tin cans and saucepans outside the house and shouting the person's name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I can't remember anybody having to leave the neighbourhood for m
isbehaving. They used to make a lot of complaints when say a man and wife had come from the public house on a Saturday night and they used to be in a fighting mood and they'd break all their crockery and go out and buy new on a Monday, such as that. But t
he people didn't seem to hold it against them. They just accepted it because it was so regular. And after the Saturday night they were very nice people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 When I say really shocked the neighbours I mean for really bad behaviour like somebody who beat his
 wife, or kept two women in the house, or behaved generally badly. Can you remember anyone being forced to leave the neighbourhood for behaviour like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. I don't think so. I can't recall anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were you given lessons by one of your parents, a tutor or governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 About four and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 When you first started what time of the morning did you go and what time did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Nine o'clock in the mor
ning. You came home for lunch, and went back after. Lunch time from twelve 'til one, or half past one. School would close at four o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What kind of school was it that you first went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 An ordinary council school in Lawrence Road. Boys and girls mixed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you walk to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How far away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well until we went to live at Bickland Road it were only three minutes walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 But you're speaking of Bickerton Street, mainly, because that's the house you lived in most as a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Well I was in the Bluecoat School for all that time. When we went back to live in Bickerton Street when father took ill I went to St. Michaels.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 So you had more than one school before you went to the Bluecoat School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes. Lawrence Ro
ad for about six months or so, and then St. Michaels. I did about approximately fifteen to eighteen months at St. Michaels.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were they both the same types of schools, St. Michaels and Lawrence Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes. Both mixed council schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now I'm g
oing to ask you some questions and if you could apply those questions to both those two little schools, before you went to the Bluecoat. Who went with you to school when you first started, when you were four and a half?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I think it was my eldest sister used to take us. She was four and a half years older than me and she was able to look after us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What did you think of school when you first went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well I didn't like it except for the reading which I was so backward on. I was very backward on r
eading and spelling and those were the two lessons that I didn't like so it wouldn't have mattered what school I was at, it was just the same.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well apart from that, did you like or dislike school at this stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I don't think I disliked it. No. I liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now, how did you feel about the teachers in these first two schools that you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 All those I contacted were lady teachers and they seemed fair enough. Seemed to be a nice class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 In what way would they bea nice class of person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
They liked obedience, and quietness and to do as you're told and to get on with your lessons, sort of thing. They didn't seem to have any special pets or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Would you say that the teachers emphasised such things as manners, tidiness, and punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
They did seem to me to be very good. They expected good manners. Punctuality was compulsory. If you weren't there for the opening time that was it the gates were locked and you were absent. You didn't have any chance of goi
ng to a late door or anything like that. And they did seem to be rather keen on tidiness.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What about ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes they were very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 If you did something the teachers disapproved of, what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I don't think anything happened to me there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What about other children if they did something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well I never saw anything of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Can you remember at all any child being punished at these schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Not apart from getting a bit of a caning or a rap on the knuckles with a ruler of something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What would they have got that for mainly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 The state of their work, or perhaps talking, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 They would punish them for mistakes in their work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Oh yes, just rap them on their knuckles with a ruler, they never carried the cane. The head teacher had the cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Would the boys and girls get the same punishments for the same offences?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I couldn't imagine that they would because boys can stand far more punishment than girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did y
our parents show an interest in your school work - now this is the first two little schools again? Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 They used to ask you what you'd been doing but I don't know as they were keenly interested though for all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did they visit the school and meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well they didn't as far as I was concerned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did the other children in these two council schools come from similar types of home to your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 The majority, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I never noticed that. They treated everybody as one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were there any gangs or groups in the schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No I don't think so. I don't know of any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now you did go on to another school afterwards, and this was the Bluecoat School and this was a boarding school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Tell me the type of school it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Bluecoat Hospital. It weren't called school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 You were aged what when you went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Seven and a half I think it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And it was run on charitable lines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 By charity, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How many children would you say were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 250 Boys and 150 girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 For how long were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I was there 'til I was fourteen and a half. About seven and half years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Why did you go to this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Because of my father dying and there was no means by which we could be kept.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And this was the sole reason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now did you want to go or not, when you were told you were going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Well I was rather keen at first to go. I don't know whether it was the uniform that attracted me or what it was, but I seemed to be keen to want to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your mother discuss it with you before you went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Well she had discussed it with me because I had a special teacher to myself at St. Michaels School for three or four months to teach me the reading.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 But did your mother discuss your going away with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 She just told us we were going to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 There was no question of 'Do you mind'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now a typical day at the Bluecoat School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Up at six, breakfast at seven, school at eight, finish school at twelve, start again at one, and work 'til five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you have any homework to do in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
No, you didn't have any homework, because the Bluecoat School education was classed as a standard higher than the ordinary council schools. They were always a standard higher and I 
presume it was because of the long hours that you put in because Saturday was included, you went into classes on a Saturday just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What did you do on Saturday afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 School, all day. Saturday made no difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No sport or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now how much time did you have to yourself to do as you liked?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
How you mentioned that at five o'clock you had your evening meal, after you'd had that supper what were you doing with yourself, were you allowed to spend the rest of
 the time up to bedtime, which incidentally, you told me was nine in the summer and eight in the winter, could you spend the rest of the evening after your evening meal doing what you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Just according to the weather, you did as you liked; just a
s long as you didn't do anything the teachers disapproved of, you did as you liked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now how often were you allowed out for walks, to church, visits to home or friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 We were allowed home for two weeks and three days, twice a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now apa
rt from that, were there any other occasions when you were allowed to visit friends or your relatives or go out for walks or go to Church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. The church was all in the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 All in the school and you were never allowed out of the school apart from those times you went home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
There was a few isolated occasions when we were taken to Calderstones Park there was some sort of a show that was on and apart from that and the one day out to Beaumaris there was nothing. As I said the bandsmen they went twice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And you weren't allowed home at weekends then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were you allowed to wear your own clothes rather than uniform at any time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. You didn't have any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 You didn't possess any clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No you didn't have anything at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now what about personal possessions? Were you allowed to own anything personal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
All the boys and girls had their own lockers. When you went into the school after the holidays you emptied your box and you put your things in your locker. B
ut it wasn't locked at all, it was just closed over. Such as your blacking brushes, blacking, and clothes brush.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What about all your treasures that you kept? Your collection of butterflies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 You'd keep them in as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were they fairly safe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes. They didn't seem to bother taking anything off each other. Course they all had the same things so it wasn't necessary.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your parents visit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. They came on Sundays to church but they weren't allowed to speak to us. They only
 came Sundays, except Prize Day. That was a day off from school for the prize presenting and the parents were invited then and they witnessed the prize distribution and they had a few sports on the field and we were allowed to talk to them then on that on
e day only, in July.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were you homesick for anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well we used to shed a few tears when we went back after the holidays, but you got over it and you came back to the general routine then.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What did you miss most?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well you didn't have the love and care and attention. It was all there but you didn't seem to have that, you had to do it for yourself.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And this was what you missed most? They care and attention that you felt your mother gave you at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 That's right. She'd give y
ou plenty of care and attention and look after you whereas in the Bluecoat you had to look after yourself. You had to make your own beds and clean the dormitories, and clean the whole building.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your mother write letters to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 On occasions, but not much. I'd say about four a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Would you write back to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Oh no, you weren't allowed. I think we were allowed to send two letters a year and that was a week before breaking up for our vacation and just let them know we'd be coming home on that day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Do you think it changed how you felt about your mother, going away to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No I don't think so. I was always grateful to my mother and I accepted the circumstances we had to put up with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you feel more or less close to her or much the same? When you came home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I'd say much the same. I never seemed to change my opinion at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did going to school change your attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes. They taught me manners and discipline that you wouldn't get ou
tside. You wouldn't even get it off your own parents. It seemed to be above proportion, it was very high. Even today at my age I address people as 'sir' if I don't know them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you meet children of a sort you had not met before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes. They cam
e from all over Liverpool and some places just outside Liverpool. The difference was with the age, the senior and the junior. They seemed to keep themselves to themselves - they seniors can play and the juniors can play and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Apart from that, were they a different type of child? Do you feel they came from the same sort of home as you did generally or not?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 The majority, yes. They were very careful and very keen by accepting a child into the school. You had to go and sit before a Committee 
and there had to be letters of recommendation from some party or another and they were very keen. They gave you a good going over before they accepted you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now when you came home on holidays did you spend your time differently from how you had before you went to this School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Well I wouldn't really know that because I was so young when I went in. And although mother was out working the sister and I were both there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 So you don't recall anything different at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No I don't know as I did. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How did you play with the same friends as before or did you have new friends when you came home? On holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 The same ones. But it's amazing how many people used to stop you being in the Bluecoat uniform and just have a few words with you a
nd whether the uniform attracted them or not I wouldn't know, or whether it was a part of sympathy I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And did you find you were playing with the same friends or not when you came home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Oh yes, playing with the same ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now you'
ve already told me what you thought of the school haven't you. Generally speaking you've said that it's given you discipline and taught you to have good manners, and it gave you a good education, and you felt the teaching was good. But you felt that the d
iscipline was a bit strict and you felt that they were rather brutal in their punishments.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 You sort of looked to them as somebody. The very few teachers that there were in the school you looked up to them. The
y were good educated people like and they knew what they were talking about, etc.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
You respected them and you looked up to them and you appreciated the fact that they were educated. Were you ever able to talk to them and get their advice or if you had any little worry were you ever able to talk to any particular one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Well one teacher in particular, and he was the head teacher, not the headmaster. You could always go and ask him for a little bit of advice if you wanted he was a person like that. H
e was approachable. The others, didn't seem so, although they were approachable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 You didn't feel you could go and talk to anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And did you avail yourself of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 On a few occasions I went and see him. Tapped on his study door and went and seen him, and he gave me the advice I needed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Obviously they accentuated the things that I've mentioned in your earlier schools, manners of course, tidiness and punctuality and ways of speaking. What about ways of speaking in the Bluecoat School did they accentuate this at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 They only wanted to try to teach you plain English.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you have any elocution lessons or anything like that at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 We've talked a lot about punishment so I won't ask the question
 about that. Tell me, did your mother show an interest in your school work whilst you were at the Bluecoat School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well she never seen any of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did she ever talk to you about it when you came home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. The only comment that she used to pass was 'I noticed you weren't amongst the prizes.' And that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did she ever have an opportunity to meet the teachers of the school? She came up on the Sundays and she cameup for Prize Giving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 She met them, but no conversation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 She didn't talk about you to the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Practically, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 At the Bluecoat School did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No I don't think so. They was pretty stern with their punishment for those that was misbehaving themselves and I was one of those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were there any gangs or groups at the Bluecoat School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I'd say yes, there were. I don't know why but t
here always seemed to be certain little gangs that used to gang up together and more often or not they just didn't take any interest in anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 They didn't have any bullying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. No bullying, nothing like that. But they used to keep to themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now you were fourteen and a half when you left school. Would you have stayed longer if you had had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No I had the opportunity and wouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you attend any part-time education afterwards, for example, any evening classes after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. I went to night school studying for shorthand typing and book keeping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How many nights a week would you have done that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 One night a week for
 twelve months. This night school was held and I think I went there 'til I was seventeen. Two years and perhaps a little bit longer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No, none regarding my education.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Oh yes I think so, yes. In great many ways. In all ways, I think I benefited
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 In what ways would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 The education was very good. I think I was very interested in all the lessons although as I say I was backward o
n the reading. But I was quite satisfied. I think it stood me well later on in life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 While you were at school did you have a part-time job or any means of earning a little regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now I should like to ask you about your first full time job. What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
At fourteen and a half, I started with the Shropshire Union Railway Canal in Man Island at the pier head. They had an office there, and dock and warehouse. I started there as a messenger boy delivering invoice notes round to the shipping people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How did you get that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Through the education. My mother took me to the education committee in Dale Street and that was one of the vacancies. The first one that they gave mother the letter to go for an interview. And th
e manager then he seemed rather a nice chap and so I took the first job that came.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What exactly did you have to do in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I was a messenger boy. You had to make out all your own copies from the invoices and then sort 'em out to go on your 
round. There was none posted, they were all hand delivered and the majority you had to get a signature for. You were practically out all day. Out all morning and you got back for your lunch and you got a fresh batch then and you went out the same thing. A
t night time I had to go up to Salisbury Dock, Clarence Dock and Brocklebank Dock where they had two wharf depots and collect the invoices for them and bring them back. That would be in the region of about six thirty or seven o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 So you started work at what time in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I had to be at Lime Street Station at eight o'clock to collect all the letters from the station.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What time would you have packed in for lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 You had an hour, twelve 'til one o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And you worked from one 'til when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 'Til you finished which was invariably half past six or seven o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What about Sundays and Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Saturdays was the same only you finished at one o'clock. You didn't work Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you have a half day during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Only Saturday afternoons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Oh yes, they were all with pay.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 What were you paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Six shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you feel that was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 It seemed average with the
 majority of boys that were working. Mother took 5/6 and I got 6d. And I could either walk to work or ride to work, but I had to walk one way. I only got a penny for the tram. The 6d I got was for my fares.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Do you didn't have any money to spend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. None at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How long did she take this 5/6 from you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 About eighteen months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Very good. I think I was looked upon as something out of the usual as I was so eager and keen,
 which still brings it back to the Bluecoat education and the discipline and the way of getting on with the job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 You didn't really see him. He was in his own private office. But they treated me pretty fair I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I liked him when I first saw him but apart from that I hardly ever saw him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How did you feel about the work you had to do? Did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I did like it at first but then I found it was ve
ry tiring because some of the treatment you met in these big offices were, where they had lifts and you had to go to the sixth floor they wouldn't let messenger boys in the lifts, you had to go up the steps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did the job alter your attitude to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
No I don't think so. Although, I was repeatedly told I had been foolish getting the job on my own 'cos they would have placed me in an office somewhere but they did place all the children - all the boys were placed into pretty good offices.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Where did you go from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
I was three weeks out of work and then I went to Brunswick Dock to what was then the Great Central Railway Loco Sheds and I started there as an engine cleaner.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And how long were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I started there in September 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 When did you start your other job, in 1915; and you were at that one job for four years, were you, the first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes I was at the same job all the time until this chap came back out of the army and they couldn't do anything about me 
except put me out. They couldn't reduce me I'd gone that far advanced, although I was still only a boy. I was only eighteen and still classed as a boy but they couldn't reduce me. I applied for various jobs in shipping offices, etc. but there was too much
 unemployed at the time, you hadn't got an earthly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
So really between the time you left school, which was 1915, and up 'til the end of 1918, you were still at this first job where you were a messenger boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now what jobs have you done since the First World War?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
I started with the Shropshire Union Railway Canal and then I went on to the Great Central Railway, which was all railway work. I started as engine cleaner, and eventually became a pass fireman (that was a spare fireman) and then became 
a full time fireman, then a spare driver, and then a regular driver. So all told, including the Shropshire Union Railway and Canal, I did 51 1/2 years service. I got a gold watch at 45 years service, nothing else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 So really from then until you retired you worked on the railway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 A railway man all my life and finished up as a driver.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. I thoroughly enjoyed my life on the railway as a fireman and driver. Thoroughly enjoyed it because 
you were travelling all the time and seeing different things all the time. I was very keen, and I never lost a day, and I was never late. The first time I lost work was when I had this heart attack and that was 1956.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you serve an apprenticeship or training period for any of your jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Yes. I served an apprenticeship with the locomotive, starting as a cleaner and working yourself up. You're serving your apprenticeship to become a driver, you've got to go through that, you couldn't become a driver without.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you belong to any trade union or professional organization?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes trade union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you take part in any of its activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Only so far as I never missed a monthly meeting. I paid into it as a member and I wanted to know what was going on concerning the job.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Incidentally, I was talking about the apprenticeship or training period. Would you have said that you would have had to have had an apprenticeship for your messenger boy days or would that not have applied in that case?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well the same thing did apply, even as a messenger, because you worked your way up and had there been vacancies you went up and up.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And did you belong to a trade union in that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes, I belonged to the Railway Clerks Association. And then the Amalgamated Society of Locomotive Engine Drivers, Firemen and Cleaners.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you take part in the first union's activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. I didn't really. I don't think there was anybody in the office that was really interested, except in pa
ying their subscriptions and I used to take their subscriptions to the union secretary who lived in Lark Lane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different ones up to 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I think they had then, but they haven't now. Over the years it has deteriorated
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest among workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes there was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Some people say that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers. Did you feel that or not?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Oh there was. The driver he was a big noise - he felt he was a craftsman. In the days when I first started there there was no such thing as uniform and the drivers used to go to work with bowler hats, and they thought they were just somebody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Well there's not many chaps will tackle the railway in the locomotive department because you have most ridiculous hours, shocking. We used to be cal
led out at a minute's notice. Many a time when we were first married I'd be getting undressed to go to bed, there would be a knock on the door, turn out at one o'clock in the morning. Just half an hour's notice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I'd like to ask you about your home life after you left school. Did you continue to live at home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your mother at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Or with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No I don't think so. I d
idn't see much of my sisters, they were in service, and they only got one day off a month, and one evening a week. So I saw very little of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you spend your Sunday any differently? Than you had done previously to leaving School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I went to Church in the morning, Sunday School in the afternoon, and Church in the Evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 This was after you left school and had started working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And up to what age would you have gone to Sunday School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well I did attend Church regul
ar, up to almost getting married, the Church of England. The same Church as I went to before I went to Bluecoat School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you take an interest in politics in this stage in your life when you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No, not really. Apart from voting, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you vote in a General Election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No because of my age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
If you had been old enough to vote, in your first job for instance, would you have felt under any pressure from anybody to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No I don't 
think so. I would definitely have not voted for the conservatives for some of the things that I had heard of when these big shipping magnates and big firms and such like how they used to bribe their employers into voting for them. For this ward R.P. Howso
n, he had his own shipping firm, and he used to give all his workers, dockers and all them, a dinner a few days before voting time and perhaps a smoke and a drink, and such like, and if he found out they hadn't voted for him they got sacked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 So pressure was put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes pressure was put on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Now would you have felt pressure was put on if you'd been old enough to vote in your firm from your employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No there was no such thing as pressure on the jobs that I was on.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 And did this go on for one political party more than another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Well that's what I thought at any rate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 You felt the conservatives pulled this rather than the labour government?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes, because the conservatives had practically ruled the country for many years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Why would you have never voted conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
I had nothing against them really, except that I'd heard about this bribery and that made me feel bitter towards them, that they weren't going in on their merits. That was the only reason.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Were you ever a member of a political party at that working time in your life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I used to pay a political levy through the trade union. You paid 1d a week and it went towards the political side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you ever work for one of the parties at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Apart from voting, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 You told me earlier something of how you spent your spare time, you collected butterflies and stamps and you played chess. Did you con
tinue to spend your spare time in the same way, or did you do different things now you'd left school and were working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I carried on collecting foreign stamps and I did carry on butterflies for a bit but I think all my enthusiasm was put to the Boys' 
Brigade, I was very interested in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you go out in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Only just knocked about locally as far as Sefton Park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Who did you go out with when you went to Sefton Park in your early working days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 With two or three of the boys of the neighbourhood. And I used to do a lot of cycling with the chap who lived in the next street to us.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you make any new friends - boys or girls - at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 I made new girl friends, but not boys - I stuck to my old mates.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 How did you meet them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 They belonged to the neighbourhood and I made these new friends through the neighbours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you bring friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 No. No friends came home, only my own cousins. I didn't start bringing a girl home 'til I was courting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did you have any special friends at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Only the one special one and he was the one I went cycling with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Yes she would meet them in the street because they were neighbours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16400881 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 Did they expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4551459 GD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740967\charrsid11091265 
Up to when I was 18 and over, and beyond that, I used to stick to my 'Bluecoat times' - still 8 o'clock in winter and 9 o'clock in summer. I liked my bed. She (his mother) automatically expected me to come home at usual tim
e. If I didn't get home at usual time, she would start to worry.
\par }}